{
  "stem": "13258.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Well, in 1943, the Germans discovered the graves at [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Katin ?], accused the Russians of having murdered thousands of Polish officers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And I won't mention the number, because numbers we hear aren't very different.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "It varies between 5,000 and 10,000.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "The Soviets said they were murdered by the Russians-- by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "The Polish exiled government in London demands an explanation, which drives the Soviets mad.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And first of all, they close all the temporary consulates, which, in the meantime, had opened, but were called, still, only delegations of the embassy.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "They arrested their heads, and they called all those people, like us, who had those temporary documents not exchanged into passports to the police and told them, from today on, you are Soviet citizens.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And within a short time, we were given some-- the explanations there were were ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "They said, you were in Tarnopol at the day when there was an election.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "I said, we were not, did not vote on that election.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "They said, that doesn't mean anything, but you were there when the people of Tarnopol voted to be united with the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now, not only was I-- the moment I became a Soviet Citizen, against my will, I also became eligible for the draft.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As long as I was a Polish citizen, I was not.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so shortly later, about a few weeks later, we are called up to the draft board.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I am given, being given 1A, being a young boy, 22-years-old, reasonably healthy, and my father, 4F.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A few weeks later, I am called to the office-- military office there, and after a lengthy interview with an officer, at which time I was asked if I would serve in the army, I said, if I'm needed, I go.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
